CS5200 - Programming Assignment 2
Student ID: 700794792
Title: Flask-Based Multi-User Notes Application with Natural Language CRUD Integration
Overview
This project implements a web-based notes management application using Flask (Python) and SQLite. Each user can register, log in, create, view, update, and delete notes. Additionally, users can perform CRUD operations using natural language commands, which are processed by either a rule-based text parser or an optional open-source LLM integration via llm_integration.py.
Project Structure

700794792_PROGRAMMING_ASSIGNMENT2/
│
├── app.py                   # Main Flask application
├── models.py                # Database models (User & Note)
├── llm_integration.py       # Handles natural language CRUD or connects to an LLM
├── db_init.sql              # SQL script to initialize the database
├── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies
├── notes.db                 # SQLite database (auto-created if missing)
│
├── templates/
│   └── index.html           # Frontend UI (login, notes, LLM interface)
│
└── static/
    └── main.js              # Frontend JavaScript (fetch API calls)

Installation Instructions
Step 1 — Prerequisites:
• Windows 10 or higher
• Python 3.12+
• Visual Studio Code (recommended)
Step 2 — Setup Virtual Environment:
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
Step 3 — Install Dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
If LLM compilation fails, use:
pip install Flask SQLAlchemy Flask-Login Flask-WTF python-dotenv
Step 4 — Initialize Database:
Option 1: python init_db.py
Option 2: python -c "from models import init_db; init_db(); print('✅ Database created successfully')"
Step 5 — Run Flask Server:
python app.py
Then open: http://127.0.0.1:5000
Usage Guide
1. Register/Login using username and password.
2. Create notes by entering topic and message.
3. View all notes via Refresh.
4. Delete/Update via natural language commands like:
   create note about Shopping: Buy milk
   list notes
   update note 1 set message to Buy bread
   delete note 2
Features Implemented
•	Multi-user login - Each user has their own notes
•	SQLite database - Persistent data storage
•	Flask backend - Handles routes, sessions, API endpoints
•	HTML + JS frontend - User interface for CRUD operations
•	Natural language CRUD commands - Text-based note management
•	Optional LLM integration - For open-source model connection
Technologies Used
•	Python (Flask, SQLAlchemy)
•	SQLite3
•	HTML, CSS, JavaScript (Fetch API)
•	Optional: llama-cpp-python / Ollama for LLM
Expected Output
After launching the app:
1. User registers and logs in.
2. Creates and views notes.
3. Executes CRUD commands in natural language.
4. Notes are stored in local notes.db.
